# {name} — Agent Reference

## Command Tiers

| Tier | Prefix | Example |
|------|--------|---------|
| Eco (shared) | `---` | `{short_name} ---dev info`, `{short_name} ---test`, `{short_name} ---audit code` |
| Tool-specific | `--` | `{short_name} --<subcommand>` |
| Decorator | `-` | `{short_name} -no-warning` |
| Positional | none | `{short_name} "query text"` |

## Structure

```
tool/{name}/
├── main.py            # Entry point
├── tool.json          # Metadata & dependencies
├── logic/             # Business logic modules
├── interface/         # Public API (main.py)
│   └── main.py
├── hooks/             # Event-driven extensions
│   ├── interface/     # Hook event definitions
│   └── instance/      # Hook implementations
├── test/              # Unit tests (test_*.py)
├── data/              # Persistent data (gitignored)
├── README.md          # User docs
└── AGENT.md           # This file
```

## Development

```bash
TOOL ---dev sanity-check {name}       # Verify structure
TOOL ---dev audit-test {name}         # Audit test naming
TOOL ---audit argparse                # Three-tier conformance
```

## Config

Check `refactor_aggressiveness` before adding backward-compat shims:
```bash
TOOL ---config show
```
When `refactor_aggressiveness = 1` (default): no shims, clean breaks only.
